# Project Planning Assist

>* This prompt helps people create plans for projects

## Overview
This prompt produces a plan for people who don't know where to start, or people who want to lay things out in the most timely manner

It solves the problem of people not being organized and helps projects get done quicker and easier because of the organization

**Best For :**
- School clubs
- Fast paced event planning
- Small business planning

**Output**
-
- A typical output looks like the plan on whatever document you specify, and the people in charge of each action
- ## Quick Start
### 1. Copy the prompt
Make a plan for [project description] with deadlines, the entire project has to be done at
[timeline] and there are [how many people] working in the group. The specific roles are
[roles] Make the plan easy to read, and easy to move onto a different task. Some
examples of each of the steps of the plan are [what you want for some steps]. Make it
short and to the point for each step and make it individual to each role. Make it easy to
share with the group.
### 2. Fill in placeholders
Replace these with your specific information:
-  [Project Description]- describe the project you need help planning and the basics of it
- [timeline] - when you will start and when you need it done
- [how many people] - how many people are in the group to help with the project
- [roles] - the role of each person, names of the people and what they need to fulfil
- [what you want for some of the steps] - explain examples of different action you need to take to complete the project

